# ACTIVE ROLE REPORT — Campaign D

## RoleChSpec — the object

For a regular implicit 2-jet `(g, H)` (`q = g·g ≠ 0`), each output role `k` with `g_k ≠ 0` admits a graph chart `x_k = h(x_i, x_j)`. Its graph-normalized defining function `F_chart = z − h` has gradient `(-h_i,-h_j,1)` and a Hessian whose output row/column is zero. `RoleChSpec(g,H)` is the Campaign A channel carrier of every such chart.

`RoleChSpec` is **invariant under the defining-function gauge** `H → H + g a^T + a g^T` (CL-D1): the single-chart Campaign A carrier moves under gauge, but the graph-normalized chart is the canonical representative of the gauge orbit, so the role carrier does not move.

